<subSubSection id="C30B651B0125FFC9A20710EE9F01F823" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAE36900125FFC9A20710EE9F41F883" blockId="15.[831,1474,1535,1814]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="B965EA820125FFC9A20710EE98D4F983" bold="true" box="[831,949,1535,1558]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from the remaining cynolebiatins by the following unambiguous synapomorphies: a medial crest with a prominent ventral expansion on the palatine (
<emphasis id="B965EA820125FFC9A45F132E9EE5F9C3" box="[1383,1412,1599,1622]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">vs.</emphasis>
without ventral expansion when crest is present), eyes positioned laterally on head (
<emphasis id="B965EA820125FFC9A53E136E9F42F903" box="[1030,1059,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">vs.</emphasis>
dorsolaterally), anterior and posterior sections of the supraorbital series of neuromasts separated by an interspace (
<emphasis id="B965EA820125FFC9A53913AE9F7EF943" box="[1025,1055,1727,1750]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">vs.</emphasis>
continuous), metallic blue bars on the flank in females (
<emphasis id="B965EA820125FFC9A2CD13CE9F73F963" box="[1013,1042,1759,1782]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">vs.</emphasis>
metallic bars absent), and anal fin pink in females (
<emphasis id="B965EA820125FFC9A29813EE98DCF883" box="[928,957,1791,1814]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">vs.</emphasis>
hyaline).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAE36900125FFC9A207122E9F01F823" blockId="15.[831,1474,1854,1974]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
