<subSubSection id="C30B651B013AFFD6A1A615D39A72FE8C" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BAE3690013AFFD6A1A615D39A72FE8C" blockId="16.[158,801,194,281]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B965EA82013AFFD6A1A615D39A54FF4C" bold="true" box="[158,309,194,217]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Distribution.</emphasis>
Brazilian eastern river basins, between rio Cachoeira, Estado da 
<collectingRegion id="49D5F872013AFFD6A0BD15F39AA6FF6C" box="[389,455,226,249]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, and rio São João, Estado do 
<collectingRegion id="49D5F872013AFFD6A3C215F39A71FE8C" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30B651B013AFFD6A1A614539A70FE2C" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BAE3690013AFFD6A1A614539A70FE2C" blockId="16.[158,801,321,441]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B965EA82013AFFD6A1A614539A7AFECC" bold="true" box="[158,283,322,345]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Greek 
<emphasis id="B965EA82013AFFD6A0FC14509957FECC" box="[452,566,321,345]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">ophthamus</emphasis>
(eye) and 
<emphasis id="B965EA82013AFFD6A3A6145099BDFECC" box="[670,732,321,345]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">lebias</emphasis>
(small fish, also a name used to compose generic names of rivulids), referring to the large eyes laterally placed on head. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
